cs.CL, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.NE, cs.CV. 

This paper is about improving neural machine translation (NMT) by incorporating linguistic features. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.CL (Computation and Language), which deals with natural language processing and computational linguistics. The paper also discusses the use of neural networks, which suggests that it could also belong to cs.LG (Machine Learning), cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence), or cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing). Finally, the paper uses the WMT16 dataset, which includes image captions, suggesting that it could also belong to cs.CV (Computer Vision).
